Root cause identified in logs:
The VBT contains wrong panel identity data: parse_lfp_data: Panel manufacturer "MS_", product code 3, year 2002 → VBT describes a 2002 MS panel instead of the actual EDO EF25QBA63.E (2025)
The backlight initializes on the wrong controller: cnp_setup_backlight: Using native PCH PWM (controller=0) intel_backlight_setup: backlight initialized, disabled, brightness 0/192000 → Starts at 0/disabled but physical panel stays at 100% duty cycle
Writing any value to /sys/class/backlight/intel_backlight/brightness updates the sysfs value correctly but has zero effect on the physical panel.
This confirms a VBT panel mapping error in firmware T4CN38WW (Lenovo Legion 5 15IPH11, model 83RW): the PWM signal is not routed to the EDO EF25QBA63.E panel controller.
